version_description: Neat formatting, two alternative ways to play it, chord legends and additional playing info included.
I'm fairly sure the JT version is at capo 2.
Dropped D tuning, neat accurate formatting, chord legend included.
There are not any other easily accessible versions of this tab on the website. It's a nice song often forgotten from Mr. Taylor's catalogue.

This acoustic version plays well, scrolls evenly, and sounds great with only one or two musicians. Chords are accurately placed, if a chord appears before the word below, then it is played before the word is sung.
Complete lyrics and chords for the Garfunkel/Taylor/Simon version which differ considerably from Sam Cook's original / https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T0bU9llGUic.
Chords and structure like the original song standard tuning - no capo.
No capo as in original James Taylor's version. At the biginning added only few specific chords.
This version reflects my performance of the song which differs from the only other available version.

This song is best played by plucking the chords. Thumb on the bass strings and first, second and third fingers on the third, second and first strings and then sprinkling in some fingerpicking of the chords.
